##############################################################
#
#Setup

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context("Numeric");		# or Complex

#---------------Tolerance------------------#
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.02,
tolType=>'relative');  #relative or absolute

#-------------- Image Scaling---------------#
$imgScale = 0.16;

$height = $imgScale*3190;

$width = $imgScale*3008;
		#aspect ratio

#---- Random variables for this problem --------#
$d1 = random(0.4, 0.6, 0.1);
$d2 = random(1.75, 2.5, 0.25);
$d3 = $d2 - random(0.25, 0.5, 0.25);
$d4 = $d3 - 0.25;

$m = random(15, 25, 5);
$g = 9.81;

#---- Formulas to compute answers --------------#
$BC = ($d1^2 + $d4^2)^(0.5);
$T_BC = $BC * $m * $g / (2 * ($d1 + $d2));
$Ay = $d4 / $BC * $T_BC;
$Az = $m * $g - $d1 / $BC * $T_BC;
$N_B = $d3 / $BC * $T_BC;
$Ax = - $N_B;

#---- Answers to the problem -----------------------#
$ansA = $Ax;
$ansB = $Ay;
$ansC = $Az;

$ansD = $N_B;
$ansE = $T_BC;

########################################################
#PGML

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "21-S-5.7-RP-04.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A smooth leaning rod has a uniform mass [`m = [$m] \: \textrm{kg}`] and is supported by a ball-and-socket joint at point [`A`], the wall at point [`B`], and a cable [`BC`]. Find the reaction components of the supports. Assume [`g = 9.81 \: \textrm{N/kg}`] and that the wall is frictionless. Let reaction components be positive if pointing along the positive axes.

Use the following values:

[`d_1 = [$d1] \: \textrm{m}`]

[`d_2 = [$d2] \: \textrm{m}`]

[`d_3 = [$d3] \: \textrm{m}`]

[`d_4 = [$d4] \: \textrm{m}`]


[`A_x =`] [___]{"$ansA"} [`\: \textrm{N}`]

[`A_y =`] [___]{"$ansB"} [`\: \textrm{N}`]

[`A_z =`] [___]{"$ansC"} [`\: \textrm{N}`]

[`N_B =`] [___]{"$ansD"} [`\: \textrm{N}`]

[`T_{BC} =`] [___]{"$ansE"} [`\: \textrm{N}`]


END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

